cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper deals with deep learning methods for recognizing object instances from a single training example, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach for training deep learning methods, which involves using an auxiliary multi-view dataset to train the network to be robust to viewpoint changes. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deal with the development and application of machine learning algorithms. Additionally, the paper may fall under the categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.RO (Robotics), as it deals with the use of neural networks for recognizing objects and has potential applications in robotics.
